wiki.summary: “GANG GANG” features each Cactus Jack member proclaiming the relationship they have with one another and the loyalty that comes with being signed to the same label. The song’s production furthers the use of string orchestration, previously used on “JACKBOYS.” One day after the song’s release, a music video was uploaded to YouTube with visuals featuring the artists smoking and hanging out in a junkyard, where they also flex expensive cars. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “GANG GANG” features each Cactus Jack member proclaiming the relationship they have with one another and the loyalty that comes with being signed to the same label. The song’s production furthers the use of string orchestration, previously used on “JACKBOYS.” One day after the song’s release, a music video was uploaded to YouTube with visuals featuring the artists smoking and hanging out in a junkyard, where they also flex expensive cars. The track’s instrumental was first used on Mar90s‘ December 2019 track, “Blue Hunnits,” released two days before. Read more on Last.fm.
